text: White with DJ Project Elena Baltagan (born February 28, 1984), better known by her stage name Ellie White, is a Romanian house music singer and songwriter. She first entered the music industry by recording a demo for DJ Project, a Romanian dance music duo. Her song "Power of Love" ranked 46th in the Media Forest 2011 summer chart, while "Nu te mai caut" placed 100th.Media Forest - Summer Chart 2011. Media Forest. Retrieved August 2, 2015. On January 19, 2012, her single "Sete de noi" (known in English as "Forever Mine") peaked at second place in the Media Forest top 10 chart. "Sete de noi" eventually ranked 43rd in the Romanian yearly top 100 chartMedia Forest Top 2012. Media Forest. Retrieved August 2, 2015. and placed 99th in Media Forest Top Audiences chart for the first third of 2013.Top Audiențe Trimestrul I 2013. Media Forest.
